  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.7869" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>64, St. George’s Square,<lb/> 8/7/82 S. W. </dateline>
        <opener>Dear Sir/</opener>
        <p>I think it best to send back at once your valuable paper on St Thomas Patois – I took it to Dr <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2561">
Rost</persName>,<note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2561">Reinhold Rost</persName> (1822-1896), Bibliothekar u. Orientalist; vgl. HSA 09722-09797.</note> and we agree that it would not do for the Journal of the RAS<note
            n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">Man hätte gerne eine genauere Begründung für die Ablehnung erfahren. Der Gegenstand von Schuchardts Artikel passt allerdings nicht wirklich zum Profil der Zeitschrift: “The Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society has been published by the Society since 1834 and is distinguished not only by its longevity but also by its consistency in providing a forum for scholarly articles of the highest quality on South Asia, the Middle East (together with North Africa and Ethiopia), Central Asia, East Asia and South-East Asia. It publishes articles on history, archaeology, literature, language, religion and art, and reviews of books in these fields“.</note> – I asked whether the Anthropological Institute would have it, but it appears to be outside their orbit also.</p>

        <p>To me it is of great interest and as you are sure of the pages oft he Vienna Academy please let me have an early <pb
            facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> Separat-Abdruck.</p>
        <p>The Meetings of the RAS have ceased until next November: so i could not even bring the matter forward till that time which would be a bad delay.</p>
        <p>On the whole I think that it will be better for you to print in the Academy,<note n="3" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <bibl>
              <ref
                  target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.529">Schuchardt, „Kreolische Studien I. Ueber das Negerportugiesische von S. Thomé (Westafrika)“, <hi
                  rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Sitzungsberichte der philosophisch-historischen Classe der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften</hi>. Wien 101, 1882, 889-917.</ref>
            </bibl>
          </note> and then get it noticed in English papers.</p>
        <p>I am very grateful for your promised Kurze Darstellung <pb facs="#IMG.3"
            n="3"/> von der afrikanische Patois for my book: it will be a great addition to my work.<note n="4"
            place="foot" type="editorial">
            <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.7537">Cust, <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">A sketch of the modern languages of Africa</hi>, London: Trübner, 1883</ref>
            </bibl> (Trübner’s oriental series) enthält diesen Zusatz nicht. Schuchardt wird auf den S. xiii u. 48 erwähnt.</note>
        </p>
        <p>I will try and find some <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">West</hi> Indian correspondent for you</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours truly</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1346">
              <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Robert Cust</hi>
            </persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
